inn1.comm: nice start, short of a good length just outside off and shapes away just a hint, Watson thinks of playing at it initially but withdraws his bat at the right time
fullish outside off, driving length, seams away, Watson lets it be
fullish on the off stump, appears to hold its line, Watson gets forward and defends it with an open face to point

gone! Beautifully bowled, short of a good length on the off and moves away off the pitch, Watson gets back to defend but the movement produces a thick edge that's snapped comfortably at first slip by Swann
shortish again on middle and squaring him up with movement away, defended awkwardly by Ponting back to the bowler
the outside edge, short of a good length, seaming away, plays at it but the edge this time is thicker, rolls down to third man past gully for a single
it comes in, shortish outside off, a hint of inward movement, Ponting lets it go
short and wide, he's playing away from his body there as he goes for the cut, chops it down to point
much fuller this time, comes back in from a good length outside off, Ponting shoulders arms
much fuller, trying to tempt him into playing the drive, some inswing, Ponting is restrained, lets it go
runs this time, short of a good length outside off, punched through point and cover for three runs
Onions on target, full on the off stump, gets to the pitch and defends it rock solid towards extra cover
pitched up full on middle and gets that all -important movement just away from Ponting, the Australian captain, though, has it well covered, moving to the back foot and pushing it to extra cover
full on the off, some movement again, pushed through to extra cover off the front foot
back of a length, just outside off, left alone to the keeper, appeared to hold its line there
overpitched and gets the treatment, width offered, Ponting leant forward and square-drove it through point for Australia's first four
overcompensated there, full on the pads this time, bread and butter stuff for Ponting who flicks it well wide of a squarish fine leg for another four
held back the length this time, pitched it short on middle, Ponting rocks back and defends it on the pitch
driving length outside off, moving away, Paine lets it through
not this time, similar but much fuller, gets forward and just eases it through cover and point to get off the mark in style
short, too wide, restrains himself from playing the cut, wide given
identical length but much closer to the off stump, left alone to the keeper

big wicket! Onions gets his maiden ODI wicket, followed up those two shortish deliveries with one bowled on a good length just marginally outside off, Paine prodded at it as it moved away from him, got a thick edge straight to Prior
back of a length on middle, Clarke is nicely behind it and blocks it hard back to the bowler
full, just outside off, leans forward and pushes it straight to extra cover
trying to probe him outside off but  it's a little too wide, Ponting has nothing to do with it
full on the pads, doesn't learn from his mistake in the previous over, identical result, flicked away to the fine-leg boundary
alters his line, rightly so, angling it in towards middle and off, fullish, defended to midwicket from the crease
held back the length slightly, bowled at close to 88mph, moving in just a touch, Ponting watches it through to the keeper
full on the off stump, driven straight to cover off the front foot
appeal for lbw, not given, short of a good length outside off, darting back in and Ponting, trying to let it through, is rapped on the pads, would have gone over
overpitched on the off stump, pushed straight to extra cover
lands on a good length on middle and off, offers the straight bat and pushes it back to the bowler
back of a length just outside off, shoots off the pitch and carries waist-high to the keeper
short of a good length just outside off, trying to ruffle him up a little at the start, moves away just at the right time as Clarke tries to defend off the back foot, is beaten
lands on a good length just outside off, gets a stride forward and defends it to extra cover
shortish on the off stump, punched straight to Collingwood at extra cover

Ponting is saved by the inside edge, Anderson, bowling from slightly wide of the crease, angles it in towards middle, Ponting tries to drive that off the front foot past midwicket, gets a thin edge onto the pads and it rolls over behind square leg
short and wide, there to cut but Clarke isn't interested, leaves it be
too straight this time, in the right zone for Clarke who flicks it elegantly through square leg for a couple of runs

appeal for a catch, probing line just outside off and shoots away, Clarke gets forward to defend and his bat clips his pads while doing so, Anderson and Prior go up but Rauf, the umpire, has made the right call, no contact with the ball there
hurling it in just outside off, and getting it to move in, it's perilously close to the off stump as Clarke leaves it alone

appeal for lbw, the movement is working well for England here, just outside off and nipping back in to strike him on the pads in line with middle but it would have gone over, probably a bit of inside edge there as well
full on middle, closes the face and pushes it wide of midwicket for a single
held back the length a little, comes back in just a hint, wide enough for Clarke to leave it be
banged it short, just outside off and Clarke fished for it, only for it to evade him and beat the outside edge
bouncer on middle, called a wide, too high, but worth a shot once in a while to get the batsman worked up, Clarke, though, in this case, didn't have to do much to duck under it
good, testing length just outside off, gets outside the line of the off stump and defends it towards extra cover
short of a good length just outside off, shaping away from the right hander, Clarke lets it go
timed it really well, just marginally outside off, got forward and just opened the face to place it behind point to beat third man to the ropes
back of a length outside off, darts back in to strike him high on the pads, dropped on the off side, Ponting called for a single but it wasn't available
short of a length, leaving the right hander, Ponting doesn't bother playing at it
fullish outside off and comes back in, Ponting goes for the drive but the swing beats him through the gate

big appeal for a catch, angling in, lands just marginally outside off and comes in, Ponting lunges to defend, is beaten through the gate again, the ball clips the pads on the way to the keeper, hence the appeal
pushed off the front foot towards extra cover
targeting middle and off, moves away a hint, Clarke offers the straight bat but ends up getting a thick edge down to third man for a single
back of a length on middle, worked away down to fine leg for a single
slightly short on the off, gets well behind it and defends it to extra cover
bowled straight on middle, gets across and turns it down to midwicket
short of a good length outside off, pushed off the back foot to extra cover
slower one there, bowled at 76mph, Clarke waited for it and dabbed it towards extra cover
angling in towards middle and off, defends it watchfully into the off side
short and wide, cut away behind point, Bresnan runs to his right from third man, dives but can't haul it back in
full on the off stump, driven straight to midwicket
short of a good length on the off, gets back, stands tall and punches it wide of mid-off for a single
short again, pushes him back and Clarke offers the full face while playing it to mid-off
similar length, dropped hard onto the ground in the off side towards cover
short on middle, pulled away down to fine leg for a single, a nice roll of the wrists there
short of a good length on middle, moves back and turns it just wide of square leg for a single
bouncer, wide, too high, well over the head
fullish on middle, gets forward and works it down towards midwicket
targeting middle, held its line there, bowled on a good length, pushed towards mid-on
short on middle, whipped away down to fine leg for a single, Clarke gets a run
fullish on the off, pushed off the front foot towards cover

appeal for a run-out, shortish outside off, cut away behind point for a single, Ponting calls for the second but is sent back, strong throw from Denly at third man, Prior takes off the bails but Ponting is a foot in
pushed him back, bowling it a little short on the off, defended into the leg side
pitched up just on the off stump, defended forward, back to the bowler
change in line, full on middle and leg, driven straight to midwicket
Ponting cashes in on this overpitched delivery, full on middle from wide of the crease, he drives it hard and straight down the ground to beat mid-on and mid-off

stifled appeal for lbw, angling it in towards middle and leg, probably a bit of inward movement too, Ponting gets a huge stride forward while trying to defend it straight, is hit on the pads, perhaps a little high there, the stride saved him too
short of a length outside off, tries to jab it down towards point, gets an inside edge onto his pads
fullish on the off, pushed through to mid-off from the crease
aggression for Clarke, short outside off, gets back and cracks it hard through mid-off and extra cover for his first boundary, took a while to come
beaten! bowled from wide of the crease, angling in towards off and moves away, drives at it but is almost done in by the swing
short of a length on middle, pushed through to mid-on off the back foot
hurled it short outside off, pulled down to deep midwicket for a single
short of a length on middle, pushed down to mid-off
back of a length on the off, rocks back and drops it down back to the bowler
full on the off, driven through the line firmly to mid-off
short of a length on middle, gets back and turns it off his wrists into the deep for a single
angling it on the pads, shuffles just a hint and helps it on its way to the fine-leg boundary, appeared to come off the pads there but the umpire's given it as runs
overpitched outside off, driven hard but extra cover comes in way, Bopara diving to his left to save a few runs
full on the off stump, leans forward and drives it down to mid-off
on middle and leg, pushed down to mid-on this time
held back the length slightly, opened the face and guided it past point down to third man for a single
bowled at 75mph on middle, gets forward and defends it to extra cover
short of a good length on the off, rocks back and knocks it down to the bowler
full on the off, gets to the pitch and pushes it down to cover, tidy over from the local boy
short and wide, cut hard into the ground and Collingwood's in the act again, diving to his right to save a couple of runs
down the leg side, Clarke fails to make contact, Prior throws himself to his right and saves four byes, a wide given
bowled on a good length just outside off, defended hard down to extra cover
full on middle, clipped off his pads down to deep square leg for a single
fullish outside off, just pushed it gently wide of a diving Strauss at cover for a single

appeal for run-out, pushed just to the left of Strauss at extra cover and Ponting scampers through for a quick single, direct hit at the striker's end but Ponting's well in, they get another run off the ricochet
guided down to third man for a single and it's time for drinks
taps it down in front of point off the back foot
full outside off, moves away just a bit, drives hard at it, misses , Prior takes off the bails and appeals but the umpire doesn't refer it, he never left his crease
short outside off, eased off the back foot down to deep cover for a single
pushed away off the back foot down to Bopara at deep midwicket for a single

perhaps a hint of frustration there from Clarke, slower through the air this time, pitched up on middle, Clarke goes hard at it, trying to clear mid-on, mistimes it and it lands just short of the fielder
just a little wide of the off stump, opens the face and runs it down to point
short outside off, run down to third man for a single to bring up the 50-stand
pushed off the back foot down to mid-on
lands on a good length on the off, defended with a bit of a reach into the off side
shortish outside off, cut down to third man for a single
tries to jab it down to third man but it's too close to cut, gets an inside edge onto his pads
much fuller, bowled on a driving length on the off, Ponting gets well forward and defends it back to the bowler
good running, slightly short outside off, just dropped his hands on that one, playing it in front of point to squeeze a quick single
straight on middle, gets on the back foot and turns it towards midwicket
safe shot, full on middle, not quite to the pitch is Ponting, tries to clear mid-on, does so but doesn't time it well enough, just a couple
swivels and pulls it down to fine leg for a single this time
angling it in on middle and off, pushed hard but straight back to the bowler who fields well on his follow-through
too straight, worked away down to deep square leg for a single
hitting the pitch hard there, bowling from wide of the crease, defended in front of the bowler
pushed to mid-off, calls for a single but then sends back Ponting, he slides his back into the crease just in time as Swann scores a direct hit
shortish on middle, clipped down to midwicket, no single available again
a touch fuller, lands on a good length, cracked straight to point, the frustration builds
they gift a run there, slower one bowled at 75 mph, pushed wide of midwicket, Anderson fumbles while getting to it and deflects it past mid-on to concede a single to Clarke
on leg stump, glanced down to fine leg for one more
fullish on middle, uses his wrists to flick it to deep square leg for a single
goes over the top, meaty delivery outside off, full and wide, lofts it nice and clean over mid-off for a one bounce four, that'll ease the pressure a little
gets off strike by punching that wide of extra cover for a single

Ponting reaches his 68th ODI half-century by pulling a short one over square leg, bisected the gap between deep midwicket and deep square leg there, has led an excellent revival after those two early jolts
pushed through the line to long-on for a single
Clarke does the same but off the back foot, this stand is now worth 70
two more, runs coming much more easily now, punched off the back foot in that big gap between deep extra cover and long-off
short of a good length on the off, dropped down towards cover
angling it in towards middle and off, flicked down to midwicket
Clarke goes after it, gave the charge to Bresnan who bowled it short, adjusted well to pull it in front of square for a couple
slower one on the off stump, the offcutter, defended into the leg side
slower one again, Clarke, trying to be attacking, made room and tried to cart that over the covers, missed, and the ball just about managed to evade the off stump
slower one bowled short on leg stump, the offcutter, trying to work it into the leg side, is struck high on the pads
short, bowled at 62 mph, pulled down to fine leg for a single
pitched up on the off stump, eased down to long-on
gets a stride forward and defends it cautiously towards extra cover
offcutter again, turned down towards deep midwicket for just one, thinks of a second but Anderson prevents it
full, comes down the track and drives it inside out wide of extra cover for a couple of runs, they're stepping it up
turns in from outside off, chops it down to extra cover
threw it up outside off, reaches forward to defend, is struck high on the pads
flighted, defended in front of extra cover
almost dragged it on there, tried to open the face to run it past point but it turned in to take the inside edge

the bowling change works! Tossed it up outside off, landed full, Ponting went for it, looking to drive it hard past extra cover, it turned in sharply, the bat turned in his hand and he ended up scooping an easy catch to Collingwood at midwicket
round the wicket, hurling it on the off stump, guided down to short third
short of a length on the off, whipped through midwicket into the deep for a single
round the wicket to the left-hander, bowls it short outside off, pulled away wide of deep midwicket for a couple to get off the mark
held its line this time, bowled at 63.7 mph, outside off, left alone
the offcutter this time, gets back and pushes it down to mid-on
full and wide, square-drove it uppishly wide of a diving point into the deep for a couple, brings up the Australian 100
poor delivery, Hussey's taken no time to get things going here, banged in short outside off, pulled away hard and handsome through midwicket for a boundary
stifled appeal for lbw, flat, spins in from outside off, Clarke is struck on the pads while defending forward but outside the line of the off stump
quicker through the air, pushed back to the bowler
slightly short, defended off the back foot towards cover
tossed up on middle and off, swept down to long leg for a single
short of a length outside off, punched down wide of long-off for a single
bowled full on the off stump, comes down the track and drives it back to the bowler
short of a length on middle, rocks back and drops it down into the off side
punched off the back foot down towards mid-off
taps it off the back foot just wide of extra cover to sneak in a single
slower one bowled full on middle, driven through to deep midwicket for a single
shortish outside off, chops it down wide of point for a single

run-out, turned down towards short fine and calls for the single, excellent throw down to the non-striker's end as Collingwood takes down the bails to find Clarke inches short of his ground, Morgan was the fielder there
tossed up on the off stump, defended wide of extra cover to get off the mark
appeal for lbw, straight on middle, held its line, Hussy got forward to defend, was perilously close to the pads as he did so, hard to say, probably made contact with both at the same time
close shout for lbw, this one looked out, much fuller and angling in towards middle and leg, struck on the pads before the bat, huge appeal but Rauf turned it down, Hussey fortunate there
worked away into the leg side for a single
the spin does the trick again, short outside off and turned in sharply, too close to cut for White who was looking to tap it down behind point, got an inside edge onto the stumps, five down now
turning in from outside off, pushed straight to the close-in fielder off the back foot
short of a length , cut down towards deep cover for a single
short of a good length on the off, defended off the back foot onto the pitch
beaten! Short of a good length just outside off and seamed away, Hopes pushed at if off the back foot, ended up playing inside the line, and it just escaped the outside edge
beaten again, similar delivery, he tried to play at it this time, looking to run it down to third man, was playing from the crease
lands on a good length on the off, driven straight to mid-off
backs away from a pull there, bowled short outside off, thought of dealing with it but rightly left it be
threw it up on leg stump, closed the face to play it wide of midwicket for a single
full on the off, driven down to long-on for a single
threw it up on the off, just taps it between point and cover for a quick single
left it alone there, spun in quite a bit but enough from outside off
flighted outside off, driven with a reach straight to extra cover
tossed up outside off, goes for the sweep down to square leg but misses
erring in length there, short, enough time for Hussey to rock back and pull it hard through square leg for a boundary, eases the pressure somewhat
pitched up outside off, driven down towards mid-off
slightly short outside off, knocks it down towards midwicket off the back foot
short of a good length on middle, turns the face and defends it to midwicket
slower one bowled on a good length on leg stump, worked away wide of midwicket this time for a single
driven firmly but straight to mid-on, bowled full on middle and Hopes played it confidently
bowled full on leg stump, pushed gently into the leg side
misfield by Owais Shah allows them a single, tossed up, driven down to mid-off where Shah overruns the ball
threw it up outside off, drilled down towards long-on where Shah fields to a sarcastic cheer from this crowd
bowed flat, and much quicker through the air, in the blockhole on middle, dug out in the off side
full on the off, defended down towards extra cover
gets on the back foot and bunts it down to deep extra cover for a single
short of a length on leg stump, turned down to fine leg for a single
poor ball, short and wide, a gift for Hopes who cuts it off the front foot hard wide of point for a boundary
short of a good length on middle, defended off the back foot towards mid-on
absolutely smashed that but straight to Strauss at extra cover, was full and wide and he'll be disappointed for missing out
went for the drive again but missed, well collected by Prior
another misfield by Shah, full and wide, went for the drive, got a thick outside edge towards third man where Shah fumbled to allow them to come back for the second
short of a length outside off, tried to force it through the covers but mistimed it to point
tossed up on the off, defended watchfully down to extra cover
full down the leg side, clipped down to short fine where Strauss fumbles but they're unable to take the single
short on leg stump, worked away wide of midwicket for a single
reaches forward and turns the face to nudge it down wide of long leg for a couple of runs
appeal for stumping, tossed up outside off, goes for a booming drive, it turns it to beat him through the gate, Prior takes off the bails, his foot never moved, needless appeal there
full on middle, pushed down wide of Onions at long-on, enough time to come back for the second
short of a length on middle and off, pushed back to the bowler
tossed it up outside off, cracked straight to extra cover
bowled full on the off stump, driven down the ground for a single to long-off
full toss on the off stump, cracked down to long-on
quicker through the air, pushed wide of the bowler, extra cover runs in to field and prevent the single
tossed it up outside off, defended with a reach to extra cover
quicker one on middle, gets back and turns it down to midwicket

a strange dismissal that, spun in from middle and kept really low, Hopes had shuffled quite a bit and tried to get his bat down, ended up getting the leading edge as he played too early and Swann just had to take a couple of steps to his right to complete a simple catch, almost crashed into mid-on there but he had called for it
short of a good length on the off, gets forward and guides it down to point
nicely timed, full on middle and leg, drove it stylishly through the line wide of a diving mid-on, Bresnan gives chase and just manages it drag it back in, three runs
bowled flat on leg stump, defended with bat close to pads towards cover
full and wide, drove it wide of long-off for a single
flighted on the off stump, crunched down to long-off
short on middle and leg, turned wide of midwicket, calls and then sends Hussey back
pushed back to the bowler
spinning away from a good length outside off, left alone to the keeper
full on the off, defended straight to extra cover
appeal for stumping, turned away from middle, Hussey tried to work it square but the spin beat the outside edge, Prior took off the bails but Hussey's foot never left the crease
short of a length outside off, chopped down towards point
full on leg stump, tries to turn it square, is struck on the pads but it landed just outside leg
cut off the back foot wide of point for a single
angling it in towards middle, defended with a lunge to extra cover
turned off the back foot behind square, Swann continues to impress
pushed to extra cover
played back to the bowler
on a good length outside off, gets to the pitch and defends it to extra cover
gets across and drives it down the ground to long-on
delicately done, tossed up, converts it into a full toss by leaning forward, reverse-paddles it down wide of short third for three runs
short outside off, cut away hard but straight to point
threw it up on middle, gets it wide of midwicket for a quick single, a throw at the striker's end hits Hussey's bat as he tries to make it in and deflects to the long-off boundary, important runs
Johnson goes after it, bowled full outside off, Johnson took it on the half-volley and smacked it over mid-on for a boundary

he's gone now, slightly flat outside off, Johnson tried to work it into the leg side but was into the shot a little too early, the ball stopped on him a bit and turned away to catch the leading edge, Anderson at extra cover didn't have to move much
quicker delivery, turns in to rap Lee on the pads but he's outside the line
Swann gets a five-for! Tossed up outside off, Lee bends forward to defend but is bowled through the gate as it turns in
full toss on the off stump, driven down to long-off
short on the off stump, punched down to long-on to get off the mark
threw up on middle, worked away wide of long-on for a single
short of a length outside off, holds its line, left alone to the keeper
driven down to long-on for a single
short and wide, cut down hard but straight to point
tossed up outside off, defended down towards extra cover
dropped off the front foot back to the bowler
pushed of the front foot straight to midwicket
worked away through square leg for a single
tossed up outside off, leans forward and knocks it down towards short third
shot off the pitch, Hussey stood tall and dropped it down to point
hits it straight back to the bowler, tossed up on middle and just chips it back to Shah who accepts it gleefully
flat on the off stump, defended from the crease to silly point
tossed up on the off, defended to silly point again
guided down to point off the front foot
pushed off the back foot to extra cover
turns the face and defends it to midwicket
straying on leg stump, misses out on a chance to clip it down towards fine leg, misses and is hit on the pads, they squeeze a leg bye
lands on a good length on the off, defended straight to extra cover, he just needs to hang on here
targeting middle and off, bowled at 88mph, defended back to the bowler
opens the face to steer it down to third man and hand Hussey the strike
full on leg stump, in the slot for Hussey who flicks it through square leg for a boundary
poor length from Anderson, doling out freebies on leg stump, Hussey picks this up beautifully, clearing the deep square-leg boundary by a mile
defended off the back foot into the off side
fullish on the off, pushed back to the bowler
bowled on a length outside off, dragged down to mid-on for a single
Australia have been bowled out, Hussey's gone for 49. Pitched up outside off, drove it straight into the palms of Denly at mid-off

inn2.comm: short and wide, no movement there, called a wide, a little harsh there from the umpire
in the blockhole outside off, dug out into the off side
just a fraction outside off and a bit of movement away, left alone to the keeper
oversteps, short of a good length outside off, left alone to the keeper, freehit time
four byes, was bowled short outside  leg stump, Strauss shaped up for a pull, missed and so did Paine behind the stumps as he dived to his right, not a great start bu Lee here
Strauss off the mark, too short from Lee and plenty of width there as well, just chopped it between point and cover for three runs
bowled on a good length on middle, gets back and defends it with a closed face on the leg side
short of a good length on the off, gets back and drops it down short of cover
oversteps, false start, shaping away from the right hander, left alone, but another freehit, close call though
full and wide, makes room to crash that through the covers , makes no contact
bowled full on the off stump, dug out back to the bowler
short of a length this time, but a little too wide for Strauss who opts out of the cut shot, called a wide
on target now, bowled on a good length on middle, defended with a full face back to the bowler
short and wide, goes for the cut, makes no contact, was there to hit but the away movement took it past him
not much movement, full on the off, driven back to Hilfenhaus who fields it well on his follow through
short of a good length outside off, cracked off the back foot straight to extra cover
nice shape away from the batsman this time, tempting him as well but a fullish delivery, Denly lets it go
short on leg stump, tries to turn it off his hips, is struck on the thighs
slightly short on middle and off, moves back and punches that wide of extra cover but a diving stop prevents the single
fullish on the off, drives it from the crease straight to midwicket
slightly short on the off, gets on the back foot and jabs it in front of extra cover
moves towards a good length ball outside off, the bat turns in his hand and it rolls over to mid-on
fullish on the off stump, again holding its line, defended back to the bowler
pitched up outside off, driven through the line to mid-off
runs, bowled full on middle, too straight, driven firmly between mid-on and midwicket, Clarke gives chance and flips it back but the batsmen have taken three
oversteps again, in the blockhole on leg stump, would have slid down as it struck him on the pads, a massive no ball there, freehit again
Strauss takes advantage of it this time, had missed out on the previous two, bowled full on middle and off, shuffles across and scoops it over short fine for a boundary
in the channel just a fraction outside off, defended to cover
pitched up on the off stump, opts to defend, dropping it towards extra cover
short of a good length on the off, Denly gets forward and defends it to cover
that beat everything! Swung in, Denly ended up playing for no movement as has been the trend this innings, zipped through the gate to just miss off stump
short of a good length on middle, gets off the mark by working it past wicket for a single, he'll be relieved
hitting a good length outside off and gets a hint of away movement to beat the outside edge as Strauss fishes for it
another wide, banged in short outside off, tries to pull it fine, misses, but it's down the leg side so Rauf calls it
a bit of a walk across from Strauss, it's aimed at the off stump, defended to the left of Lee
nicely done, just a hint of width and he punches it from the crease through the covers for a couple
bowled full on the off, driven straight to mid-on off the front foot
short of a good length on middle, rocks back and defends it down the pitch
a touch fuller, Denly again opts to play it off the back foot, knocking it back to Hilfenhaus
a costly no-ball, full and wide, driven elegantly through the off side between mid-off and extra cover, four for Denly
pitched up on middle, Denly makes way and drives it from the crease hard and wide of mid-on for a boundary, expensive over this
another no-ball, big one too, short on the off, defended to extra cover, freehit
beamer, darts at Denly's head and he manages to evade it just in time, the bowler apologises but the freehit from the previous ball still holds
caught off a freehit, full and wide, drives it straight to mid-off but that can't be out
short of a good length on the off, moves back and defends it towards cover
slower one bowled full on the off, defended into the leg side
bowled on a driving length outside off, Strauss isn;'t sucked in, shoulders his arms
beaten, back of a length just outside off, holds its line but Strauss tries to defend inside the line
chopped off the back foot straight to extra cover
angling it in towards middle, works it from the crease just wide of the bowler
slightly short on the off, cramping him for room there so Strauss just drops it back to Lee
just a hint of away movement, tries to jab it off the back foot, gets a thick outside edge down to third man for a single
erring in length and pays the price, short on the off, Strauss is onto it quickly, pulling it away through midwicket for four runs
uppish, full outside off, slices it over the fielder at point for a single down to third man
nips back in from a good length outside off, defended off the back foot onto the pitch
excellent yorker there from Hilfenhaus, dug out onto the pitch, got his bat down just at the last moment
shot! Just a fraction overpitched and Denly gives it the treatment, driving it with a full face wide of the bowler and past mid-on for a boundary
slower one bowled short just outside off, drops his hands on that one and squeezes a single behind point
lands on a good length on the off, stays in his crease and defends it to cover
beaten, moving off the pitch, drives through the line but doesn't expect the movement
short of a length outside off, tries to cut it hard through point but makes no contact
aiming at middle and off, gets on the back foot and dabs it towards point
short of a good length on middle, gets behind it and drops it back on the pitch
short of a good length on the off, rocks back and taps it to extra cover
forces it hard off the back foot but Ponting's prowling at extra cover, fields it sharply to prevent any runs
lands on a good length on middle, opts to stay in the crease and defends it to cover
driven hard but to cover, full and wide and he went after it, connect superbly but was unable to find the gap
offers the full face as he defends that to extra cover
played it nicely, slightly short and some width, opened the face at the last moment to run it past point to third man for a single
tossed up on the off, defends with bat close to pad towards extra cover
round the wicket to Strauss, angling in towards middle, defended off the front foot to extra cover
went straight on, Strauss expected it to turn away but it held its line, wrong judgment there, just missed the off stump
worked away to square leg, thinks of a single but then sends his partner back
threw it up on middle, swept it hard square, wide of fine leg for a couple of runs

appeal for lbw and a catch, fires it in on leg stump from round the wicket, the quicker one, Strauss is rapped on the pads as he tries to play it off the back foot, it lobs up and ends in White's hands at slip
fullish on the off, driven straight to mid-off
slightly short on middle, turned of the back foot to square leg
bowled full on the off stump, tries to drive it hard and straight, ends up getting a thick outside edge just wide of third man for a couple, 50 up
short of a length, chops it down towards cover
beautifully timed, short of a good length on middle, rocks onto the back foot and just tucks it through square leg, fine leg running across had no chance
back of a length on the off, gets back and defends it to point
left alone, spun away from a good length outside off
pushed through to extra cover
full on middle, drops it dead on the pitch
swept down to deep square leg for a single
flighted, bowled full on the off, turned wide of midwicket for one more
the straighter one, short on the off, moves away slightly and cuts it behind point for a single
shuffles across, it's bowled full on the off stump, defended back to the bowler
punished, short and wide, the field is up, Strauss crashes it through point for a boundary
bowled at 91.8 mph, lands on a good length just outside off, defends it with a closed face back to the bowler
banged in short outside off, a touch too wide, the umpire calls it, another extra delivery
another terrible delivery, short outside leg stump, Strauss walks across and taps it down to the fine-leg boundary
wide down the leg side, slower ball gone bad, misdirected
short again, on middle, pats it down to fine leg for a single
too much width, much fuller, square-driven by Denly past point, third man has no chance, another four, Australia looking out of it here
thinks of the sweep but adjusts his shot as it's too full, defends it to midwicket
tossed up outside off, guided down to point
short outside off, held its line, cut away hard behind point for a couple
tossed up outside off, steered past point for a single this time
Denly tries to go over the top, flighted and full on the off stump, appeared as if he wanted to clear mid-on but he wasn't in control there, mistimed it to deep midwicket
full outside off, eased off the front foot through the covers for a single
bowled at 89.5 mph, full on middle, driven straight to midwicket
shortish on middle, worked away down to square leg for a single
full on the off stump, just pats it past the bowler in front of mid-off for a single
too full, meaty length outside leg stump, tickled down to fine leg for a single
bowled full on middle, defended back to the bowler
short of a good length outside off, mistimes an attempted drive to extra cover
slightly short on the off, punched off the back foot to the bowler
slower through the air, pushed between point and cover for a single
flighted just outside off, worked away down to long leg for a single
pitched full outside leg and turned in, Strauss was hit on the pads as he tried to work that away
threw it up outside off, turned away, left alone
bowled full and quick outside off, steered it past point for a couple more
short of a good length on the off, rocks back and knocks it down
back of a length on middle, turned wide of mid-on for an easy single
short of a good length outside off, punched wide of a diving extra cover for a single
stylishly played but didn't find the gap, full and wide, thumped it to extra cover, Ponting fumbled slightly, diving to his right, allowing them a single
slower one bowled short on middle, gets back, rolls his wrists over, and gets a single behind square
just a fraction short outside off, clanked it straight to point
no-ball from Hauritz, he joins the party, tossed up outside off, steered down to deep point for a single, a tough call there, was very marginal, freehit
Denly will be cursing himself there, tossed it up on middle, goes for the slog-sweep, it was there to be smashed, but he was deceived by the lack of pace there, took forever to get to him
slightly short on the off, rocks back and forces it wide of extra cover who gets a hand to it and keeps them down to a single
spins away, Strauss goes for the sweep and misses
connects this time, sweeping it through square for a single
flighted on middle, driven just wide of long-on for a single to keep the strike
short of a good length outside off, bowled at 81.5 mph, chopped down to point
punches it from the crease towards deep cover for a single
tucks it down towards fine leg, slightly short on the off
fraction short and Denly capitalises, seizing the length early to pull it away over midwicket, 100 up
short of a good length on middle, defended off the back foot back to the bowler
nicely timed, four more, short of a good length outside off, waited for it and steered it elegantly behind point, it's a quick outfield and the ball just raced away
worked down to long leg for a single
tossed it up outside off, goes for the slog-sweep and not for the first time this game, he misses

one down! The frustration of not getting the sweep right appears to have got to him, it's flighted outside off, goes for the reverse-sweep, ends up getting a top edge straight to Hilfenhaus at short third man
flighted outside off, gets across to drive it past midwicket, gets an inside edge onto his pads
threw it up, bowled it really slow, comes down the pitch and defends that to midwicket
short of a good length on the off, pushed through to extra cover
stopped on him a little there, and he was a touch surprised by the bounce, played it uppishly towards midwicket
tried to play it down to third man and was beaten for pace there
worked away off the back foot down to deep midwicket for a single
full on the off, driven through the line back to the bowler
off to a positive start, short outside off, made it seem as if he had all the time in the world to play it, pulled it away nonchalantly over midwicket
turns him and catches him on the pads, but he was outside the line
short on middle, worked away to deep square leg for a single
pushed it quick, defended off the back foot to the bowler
turning in from a good length outside off, worked behind square leg for a single
threw it up outside off, turned it behind square, one more
bowled full on middle, played straight to midwicket
lands on a good length outside off, tries to drive it past cover, misses
a touch too wide there, had to reach for it, played it straight to extra cover
short of a length on the off, punched back to the bowler
too straight, flicked straight to midwicket though
played off the back foot down towards mid-on
short of a good length on the off, defended back on the pitch
flighted outside off, went for the drive, the bat hit the ground as he tried to drive it hard through cover
pushed through to extra cover
worked away through square leg for a single
full and wide, Bopara took it on the half-volley and caressed it past a diving extra cover for a boundary, sweetly hit, raced away
driven off the front foot into the off side for a single
short of a good length outside off, tapped down to third man for one more
reaches his half-century in streaky fashion, cut away after landing on a good length, he moved to defend it off the back foot, got a thick outside edge that beat third man to the ropes
short and wide, cracked down to deep point for a single
the legcutter again, moved across to defend it towards extra cover
cut back in this time to surprise Bopara, struck him high on the pads and lobbed up on the leg side
short of a good length on the off, punched through to deep cover for a single
cut back in, some movement off the pitch now, Bopara was late to get his bat down and it beat him through the gate
square-driven to point off the back foot, just a fraction short
darted back in again, defended back to the bowler, was in a good position to play this one, pushed it onto the pitch
eased off the front foot towards sweeper cover for a single
driven confidently down to mid-on, pitched up on the off stump

run-out, blame Ponting, short outside off, punched wide of Ponting at extra cover and they attempt a suicidal single, he picked it up cleanly and returned an accurate throw to Paine who took off the bails to find Denly well short
pushed off the front foot to extra cover, no single this time
angling in towards middle, rocks forward and  defends it to midwicket
back of a length on middle, tries to push it past the bowler, gets an inside edge onto his pads
over the top straightaway, mistimed, pitched ip outside off, just about manages to clear extra cover to earn a couple
the offcutter, waits for it and defends it with an open face towards point
fullish on the off, drops it wide of extra cover for a single
short of a good length outside off, chopped down to third man for a single
back of a length on middle and off, defended off the back foot to cover
good length on the off, leans forward to defend it back to the bowler
fullish on the off, moves forward and jabs it towards extra cover
given! Bowled on a good length on middle and leg, gets half-forward to work it square, misses and is struck plumb in front of the stumps
aggression from Shah, pitched up and he doesn't want to get bogged down, hits it hard through the line, clearing mid-off comfortably
it's getting more interesting now, short of a length outside off, tries to force it from the crease through point with a slightly opened face, gets a thin edge straight to Paine who takes a sharp one
back of a length on the off, pushed through cover for a single to get off the mark
nipped back in sharply to catch him on the pads, was a little high there, lobbed up behind point and they take a couple
back of a length on the off, defended into the off side
bowled on a good length outside off, defended watchfully to extra cover
gets on the front foot and dabs it down towards point
much fuller, pushed off the front foot back to the bowler
edged and just short, that would have made things even more interesting, full outside off, sucked into the drive, gets a thick edge inches short of a widish first slip
bowled full on middle and off, worked down to midwicket
gets forward and taps it between cover and point for a single
back of a length on the off, pushed straight to extra cover
full and wide, driven straight to extra cover, well timed but couldn't pierce the field
angling it in towards off stump, defended with a still head to the bowler
slower one bowled on a good length on the off, defended down to midwicket
Morgan goes! They've opened up the game now, short and wide, goes for the cut, gets a thick edge straight to Paine
short of a good length outside off, leaves it be wisely
bowled full on the off, moves back and defends it towards the bowler
short of a good length on the off, pushed off the back foot to cover
gift delivery on the pads, full and juicy, Collingwood flicks it away through midwicket for a much-needed, pressure-relieving four
short of a good length on the off, defended off the back foot to cover
appeal for lbw, swinging in this time to strike him on the pads but he was just outside the line as he came forward to defend
pushed off the back foot into the leg side
neatly played, short and wide, smacked into the ground and just over point but the fielder there does well to stop it short
bowled full outside off, pushed through the line just wide of Lee
the attempted bouncer, Prior does well, moving back and pulling it high over midwicket to the boundary, crucial runs these
beaten this time, bowled at 93mph, stays in his crease and without any foot movement, plays at it away from his body and misses
four more, England are racing ahead now, full outside off, squeezes it through that gap between cover and point
short of a good length on the off, pushed into the leg side towards mid-on
full on the off, pushed straight to extra cover
short of a good length on the off, defends it with a straight bat into the off side
punched off the back foot wide of mid-on for a single
angling in towards middle, bowled at 87mph, defended into the leg side
swings in, takes it off the middle stump and glances it down to fine leg for a couple of runs
bowled on a good length outside off, gets an inside edge onto his pads as he tries to defend playing forward
darting back in from a good length outside off, knocks it down towards cover
short of a length outside off, pushed wide of point for a single
back of a length on the off, defends it back on the pitch
bowling from wide of the crease and angling it in towards the off stump, gets a thick outside edge as he tries to push at it, single down to third man
commits the same mistake as Watson sometime earlier, gifts one on the pads to Collingwood, bowling to his strength there, flicked away through square leg for another boundary, the end is near now
bowls it straight on middle, Prior gets forward and works it straight to midwicket
Prior goes! Hilfenhaus makes up somewhat with an important wicket, bowled on a good length on the off, pushed through straight to Ponting at extra cover, little intent in that shot, just a chip
a bit of reverse there for the bowler, bowled full on middle, defended back to the bowler
fullish outside off, tempting him to play except that Bresnan opts to leave it alone
full on middle, driven down to mid-on from the crease
back of a length on the off, gets back and drops it in front of cover
one taken, short on middle, tucked away off his hips to fine leg
well done Bresnan, short outside off, stays his ground and pulls it down wide of mid-on for four, poor length
good length on the off stump, defended towards cover from the crease
punched off the back foot towards point
clipped away, too straight Lee and Bresnan brings the deficit to under ten by flicking it wide of fine leg
full on leg stump, struck on the pads as he attempted a similar shot, would have gone down
edged to third man, surprised by the extra bounce there was Collingwood, jabbed at it, got a single
full, just outside off, tries to drive it through cover, doesn't connect
short of a good length on the off, pushed off the back foot to cover
cuts back in just a touch, chopped down to point
four more, full and wide, goes after it, slicing it well wide of cover to bring England closer
lands on a good length on the off, defended straight to cover
bowled short on leg stump, just lifts it behind square for a single, didn't time it all that well but got a single nevertheless
goes for the pull, misses, well taken by Paine who drives to his left, belated appeal by Lee
yorker on middle, pacy but Bresnan is equal to the task, digging it out back to the bowler
misdirected bouncer, scores are level now, that was down the leg side, called by the umpire
short of a good length on middle, rocks back and defends it to midwicket
yorker again, tries to push it back towards the bowler, gets an inside edge onto his pads
full outside off, driven straight to mid-off
game over, apt end to the match as Hilfenhaus oversteps and concedes the winning run
